00:34:42,690 --> 00:34:44,329
you get from a job is something you get in the future.

538
00:34:44,330 --> 00:34:46,528
People who don't have money and aren't smart...

539
00:34:46,529 --> 00:34:47,569
always say stuff like that.

540
00:34:47,570 --> 00:34:48,699
Did he leave Ivy Class because you didn't have money?

541
00:34:48,700 --> 00:34:51,426
Guys like him have no future.

542
00:34:52,040 --> 00:34:54,160
In my point of view,

543
00:34:55,070 --> 00:34:57,679
money is an important value...

544
00:34:57,680 --> 00:34:59,326
that has formed in our society.

545
00:34:59,909 --> 00:35:02,272
And it's something we cannot go against.

546
00:35:02,850 --> 00:35:04,679
Therefore, we agree with the statement...

547
00:35:04,680 --> 00:35:08,527
that money should be our standard when choosing a job.

548
00:35:12,060 --> 00:35:13,689
We already ended transferring kids to other schools...

549
00:35:13,690 --> 00:35:15,609
regarding their change of career in the first semester.

550
00:35:15,989 --> 00:35:18,099
Yes, I know. That's why I'm here...

551
00:35:18,100 --> 00:35:19,543
meeting the principals in person.

552
00:35:20,200 --> 00:35:22,754
I'd like to receive the principal's recommendation for this issue.

553
00:35:23,170 --> 00:35:24,311
But...

554
00:35:24,440 --> 00:35:27,500
I don't understand why the chairman of a prestigious school...

555
00:35:27,710 --> 00:35:29,768
like Seolsong is so involved with the kids' transfer.

556
00:35:29,769 --> 00:35:32,264
It's natural that I step up since it's about my students.

557
00:35:33,379 --> 00:35:35,949
Our school is focused mainly on getting kids into universities.

558
00:35:35,950 --> 00:35:37,648
So the kids with bad grades seem to be getting left out,

559
00:35:37,649 --> 00:35:39,367
and that has always upset me.

560
00:35:39,619 --> 00:35:40,659
I see.

561
00:35:42,649 --> 00:35:44,189
There will be financial support...

562
00:35:44,190 --> 00:35:46,358
since I'm asking you to do a favor for our students.

563
00:35:46,359 --> 00:35:47,369
First,

564
00:35:47,529 --> 00:35:49,158
we could start off by supporting Yumin High School...

565
00:35:49,159 --> 00:35:50,644
with new tools and equipment for practice classes.

566
00:35:50,960 --> 00:35:52,413
Goodness, that's too much.

567
00:35:52,729 --> 00:35:55,228
Yumin High School has the highest employment rate in the country,

568
00:35:55,229 --> 00:35:56,341
so I'm the one that's honored to help.

569
00:35:57,639 --> 00:36:00,408
I'll try my best to make sure Seolsong High School kids...

570
00:36:00,409 --> 00:36:01,621
could get transferred to our school.

571
00:36:03,009 --> 00:36:04,091
Thank you.

572
00:36:05,040 --> 00:36:06,928
- Let's eat. - Okay.

573
00:36:12,950 --> 00:36:15,118
Now, it's time for the opposing side to make...

574
00:36:15,119 --> 00:36:16,332
their first argument.

575
00:36:17,960 --> 00:36:19,518
We disagree...

576
00:36:19,519 --> 00:36:22,155
with the statement that money should be our standard...

577
00:36:22,290 --> 00:36:23,472
when choosing a job.

578
00:36:28,229 --> 00:36:31,199
The Easterlin Paradox shows that not all rich people...

579
00:36:31,200 --> 00:36:33,190
are happy.

580
00:36:34,540 --> 00:36:37,873
The hypothesis saying a higher income will lead to happiness...

581
00:36:38,180 --> 00:36:40,849
was also proven wrong by many research...

582
00:36:40,850 --> 00:36:41,878
that have been conducted in advanced countries.

583
00:36:41,879 --> 00:36:44,679
According to the Korea Health Industry Development Institute,

584
00:36:44,680 --> 00:36:47,719
when young people search for jobs,

585
00:36:47,720 --> 00:36:50,118
the most important thing they consider...

586
00:36:50,119 --> 00:36:52,988
is the job's stability and long-term availability.

587
00:36:52,989 --> 00:36:55,488
Unlike what Young Min claimed, they considered stability...

588
00:36:55,489 --> 00:36:57,258
as the most important factor instead of high income.

589
00:36:57,259 --> 00:37:00,188
And the next factor was money.

590
00:37:00,600 --> 00:37:03,169
It seems like our peers from Wildflower Class...

591
00:37:03,170 --> 00:37:05,695
failed to do research on the most basic information.

592
00:37:09,540 --> 00:37:12,306
Please make statements that are related to the debate.

593
00:37:21,320 --> 00:37:23,340
If no one wishes to make any additional arguments,

594
00:37:23,619 --> 00:37:25,478
we'll end the debate with the final speech.

595
00:37:30,359 --> 00:37:33,228
According to Gallup and many surveys,

596
00:37:33,229 --> 00:37:36,057
our GDP has been constantly increasing...

597
00:37:36,170 --> 00:37:38,059
for the past 50 years.

598
00:37:38,300 --> 00:37:40,694
And the overall individual income has also increased.

599
00:37:40,810 --> 00:37:42,939
However, people's happiness...

600
00:37:42,940 --> 00:37:45,233
didn't increase at all.

601
00:37:46,180 --> 00:37:47,290
Therefore,

602
00:37:47,909 --> 00:37:51,081
money should not be the standard when it comes to choosing a job.

603
00:37:52,479 --> 00:37:55,318
That is the end of Ivy Class' final statement.

604
00:38:01,129 --> 00:38:03,785
Wildflower Class, please make your final statement.

605
00:38:08,029 --> 00:38:09,444
People seem to be embarrassed...

606
00:38:09,970 --> 00:38:12,364
about showing people that they think money is important.

607
00:38:12,670 --> 00:38:15,468
But you see, money is an inevitable factor in our lives.

608
00:38:15,470 --> 00:38:16,551
Right?

609
00:38:18,509 --> 00:38:20,579
Regardless of how cheap and dirty it might seem,

610
00:38:20,580 --> 00:38:21,878
trying hard to endure everything...

611
00:38:21,879 --> 00:38:23,209
because you're scared that you might lose your job,

612
00:38:23,210 --> 00:38:25,846
