613
00:38:29,290 --> 00:38:30,361
is not...

614
00:38:32,790 --> 00:38:34,910
an embarrassing thing at all.

615
00:38:36,290 --> 00:38:39,997
To be honest, I'm scared I might get fired.

616
00:38:40,999 --> 00:38:44,675
The fact that I feel so scared because of that darn money...

617
00:38:45,540 --> 00:38:46,681
makes me feel miserable.

618
00:38:50,509 --> 00:38:53,034
There are some people who disregard money...

619
00:38:53,639 --> 00:38:55,378
when they've never even earned a single penny themselves...

620
00:38:55,379 --> 00:38:57,278
and were born in a rich family...

621
00:38:57,279 --> 00:38:59,340
who are used to taking care of everything with money.

622
00:39:01,889 --> 00:39:04,388
But if you're not paid, it's not considered a job.

623
00:39:04,389 --> 00:39:06,379
It's considered as volunteer work.

624
00:39:06,460 --> 00:39:08,004
Someone once said this.

625
00:39:08,229 --> 00:39:09,689
"If you don't think you can buy happiness with money,"

626
00:39:09,690 --> 00:39:12,184
"check if you actually have enough money."

627
00:39:12,499 --> 00:39:15,297
What's the point of self-realization when you can't even get paid...

628
00:39:15,369 --> 00:39:17,087
as much as you work?

629
00:39:17,170 --> 00:39:20,200
Gosh, how materialistic. You're so shallow.

630
00:39:21,269 --> 00:39:24,541
- What? - Why did you return to school...

631
00:39:24,680 --> 00:39:26,800
at that age when it doesn't even...

632
00:39:27,379 --> 00:39:28,419
pay you any money?

633
00:39:32,820 --> 00:39:35,345
It's embarrassing, isn't it?

634
00:39:36,190 --> 00:39:37,200
Hey.

635
00:39:50,430 --> 00:39:52,792
Why do you think it's shallow to like money...

636
00:39:53,139 --> 00:39:56,069
when you're experiencing all the benefits...

637
00:39:56,369 --> 00:39:57,451
money can give you?

638
00:39:58,279 --> 00:40:01,006
